"ListParagraph"/><w:numPr><w:ilvl w:val="0"/><w:numId w:val="5"/></w:numPr><w:spacing w:after="0" w:line="240" w:lineRule="auto"/><w:contextualSpacing w:val="0"/><w:rPr><w:color w:val="2F5597"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r><w:rPr><w:color w:val="2F5597"/></w:rPr><w:t>Main Purpose (Note: this should be a short/brief description (one to two sentences only)</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="03262E18" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00D865E0" w:rsidRDefault="00D865E0" w:rsidP="00D865E0"><w:pPr><w:ind w:left="720"/><w:rPr><w:color w:val="2F5597"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r><w:rPr><w:color w:val="2F5597"/></w:rPr><w:t xml:space="preserve">In 2009–2012 the IAEA INPRO section has developed a set of Excel spreadsheets called NEST (NESA Economics Support Tool) for calculation of basic economics functions of the Nuclear Power Plants. NEST was designed to calculate </w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="gramStart"/><w:r><w:rPr><w:color w:val="2F5597"/></w:rPr><w:t>LUEC  (</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellStart"/><w:proofErr w:type="gramEnd"/><w:r><w:rPr><w:color w:val="2F5597"/></w:rPr><w:t>levelised</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellEnd"/><w:r><w:rPr><w:color w:val="2F5597"/></w:rPr><w:t xml:space="preserve"> unit electricity cost), NPV (net present value), IRR (internal rate of return), ROI (return of investment), sensitivity characteristics for different types of NPPs and fuel cycles. Excel calculations of NEST comprise a combination of ca. 50 sheets with several hundred of tables and macros. In 2014-2016 INPRO performed a benchmark of NEST against G4ECONS (a code developed by GIF EMWG). NEST calculations </w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="gramStart"/><w:r><w:rPr><w:color w:val="2F5597"/></w:rPr><w:t>requires</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="gramEnd"/><w:r><w:rPr><w:color w:val="2F5597"/></w:rPr><w:t xml:space="preserve"> some optimisation, unification of options throughout the different modules, improvement of user interface (UI), and incorporation of cost sensitivity diagram. User Technical manual needs to be developed to cover needs for the experts performing calculation as well as for those updating and maintaining the tool. The data entry, processing and storing system needs some enhancement to match with the IT changes.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="6AC30244" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00D865E0" w:rsidRPr="00A111C1" w:rsidRDefault="00D865E0" w:rsidP="00D865E0"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="ListParagraph"/><w:numPr><w:ilvl w:val="0"/><w:numId w:val="5"/></w:numPr><w:spacing w:after="0" w:line="240" w:lineRule="auto"/><w:contextualSpacing w:val="0"/><w:rPr><w:color w:val="2F5597"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="00A111C1"><w:rPr><w:color w:val="2F5597"/></w:rPr><w:t>Functions / Key Results Expected (SoW) (undergoes HR review for over 63 days):</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="563AE9B5" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="0097028F" w:rsidRPr="0097028F" w:rsidRDefault="0097028F" w:rsidP="00CE1744"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="ListParagraph"/><w:numPr><w:ilvl w:val="0"/><w:numId w:val="8"/></w:numPr><w:spacing w:after="0" w:line="240" w:lineRule="auto"/><w:rPr><w:color w:val="2F5597"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="0097028F"><w:rPr><w:color w:val="2F5597"/></w:rPr><w:t>Update user manual describing new section ‘Analysis’ of the updated NEST tool, adding section on the tool limitations (e.g. max number of cases maintained, max number of reactors in one case, ranges for basic parameters etc) and removing inconsistencies with the introduced NEST modifications.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="2D24B107" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="0097028F" w:rsidRPr="008B3E80" w:rsidRDefault="0097028F" w:rsidP="008B3E80"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="ListParagraph"/><w:numPr><w:ilvl w:val="0"/><w:numId w:val="8"/></w:numPr><w:spacing w:after="0" w:line="240" w:lineRule="auto"/><w:rPr><w:color w:val="2F5597"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="008B3E80"><w:rPr><w:color w:val="2F5597"/></w:rPr><w:t>Add new power plant types: ‘Purchase of fuel assemblies and return of spent fuel’ and ‘Renewables + back-up plant’.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="73A81F13" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="0097028F" w:rsidRPr="008B3E80" w:rsidRDefault="00B46BF4" w:rsidP="008B3E80"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="ListParagraph"/><w:numPr><w:ilvl w:val="0"/><w:numId w:val="8"/></w:numPr><w:spacing w:after="0" w:line="240" w:lineRule="auto"/><w:rPr><w:color w:val="2F5597"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="008B3E80"><w:rPr><w:color w:val="2F5597"/></w:rPr><w:t>Add c</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidR="0097028F" w:rsidRPr="008B3E80"><w:rPr><w:color w:val="2F5597"/></w:rPr><w:t>alculation of NPV, ROI and IRR. Figures of merit can be added to ‘Results’ page along with LUEC (table and graph)</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidRPr="008B3E80"><w:rPr><w:color w:val="2F5597"/></w:rPr><w:t xml:space="preserve"> or as a separate page</w:t></w:r><w:r w:rsidR="0097028F" w:rsidRPr="008B3E80"><w:rPr><w:color w:val="2F5597"/></w:rPr><w:t>.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="13BD0B53" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="0097028F" w:rsidRPr="008B3E80" w:rsidRDefault="0097028F" w:rsidP="008B3E80"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="ListParagraph"/><w:numPr><w:ilvl w:val="0"/><w:numId w:val="8"/></w:numPr><w:spacing w:after="0" w:line="240" w:lineRule="auto"/><w:rPr><w:color w:val="2F5597"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="008B3E80"><w:rPr><w:color w:val="2F5597"/></w:rPr><w:t xml:space="preserve">Implement the uniform distribution (w=1/T) for the investment schedule. Reference explaining different methods of input for the investment schedule can be provided it the user manual. </w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="56682686" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="0097028F" w:rsidRPr="008B3E80" w:rsidRDefault="00B46BF4" w:rsidP="00CE1744"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="ListParagraph"/><w:numPr><w:ilvl w:val="0"/><w:numId w:val="8"/></w:numPr><w:spacing w:after="0" w:line="240" w:lineRule="auto"/><w:rPr><w:color w:val="2F5597"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="008B3E80"><w:rPr><w:color w:val="2F5597"/></w:rPr><w:t>Add autosave function and introduce warning before